# Documentation is required for every request handler.
# Please keep this list sorted!

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CompleteBlobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CompleteBlobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Complete a blob upload that was written directly to cache, but has not yet been completed or aborted.\
This is an internal only request.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CreateBucketRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CreateBucketRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a bucket.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTBucketPUT.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CreateObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.CreateObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an S3 object in a bucket.  Include the data for the object with your request.  \
It is recommended to use DS3 requests to create a PUT job before using a PUT request to put an object in the job \
rather than using this request stand alone in a strict S3 manner.  This is particularly important when putting \
many small objects or putting very large objects that must be broken up for physical placement.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTObjectPUT.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteBucketRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteBucketRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete a bucket.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTBucketDELETE.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete an S3 object in a bucket.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTObjectDELETE.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteObjectsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.DeleteObjectsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete multiple S3 objects in a bucket.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/multiobjectdeleteapi.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetBucketRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetBucketRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get S3 objects in a bucket.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTBucketGET.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetBucketsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetBucketsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all buckets.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTServiceGET.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.GetObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the data for an S3 object in a bucket.  \
It is recommended to use DS3 requests to create a GET job before using a GET request to get an object in the job \
rather than using this request stand alone in a strict S3 manner.  This is particularly important when getting \
many small objects or getting very large objects that have been broken up for physical placement.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTObjectGET.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.HeadBucketRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.HeadBucketRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get bucket metadata key-values returned as HTTP headers.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTBucketHEAD.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.HeadObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.amazons3.HeadObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get S3 object metadata key-values returned as HTTP headers.  \
This is an AWS request \
(see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTObjectHEAD.html for AWS documentation).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateBucketAclForGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateBucketAclForGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for a bucket, granting the specified permission to the specified group.  \
Only allowed for administrators and users with OWNER access to the bucket the ACL is being created for.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateBucketAclForUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateBucketAclForUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for a bucket, granting the specified permission to the specified user.  \
Only allowed for administrators and users with OWNER access to the bucket the ACL is being created for.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateDataPolicyAclForGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateDataPolicyAclForGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for a data policy, granting the specified group access to use the data policy.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateDataPolicyAclForUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateDataPolicyAclForUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for a data policy, granting the specified user access to use the data policy.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalBucketAclForGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalBucketAclForGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for all buckets current and future, granting the specified permission to the specified group.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalBucketAclForUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalBucketAclForUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for all buckets current and future, granting the specified permission to the specified user.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalDataPolicyAclForGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalDataPolicyAclForGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for all data policies current and future, granting the specified group access to use any data policy.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalDataPolicyAclForUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.CreateGlobalDataPolicyAclForUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create an ACL for all data policies current and future, granting the specified user access to use any data policy.  \
Only allowed for administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.DeleteBucketAclRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.DeleteBucketAclRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified bucket ACL.  \
If the ACL being deleted is global (applies across all buckets), the operation is only allowed for administrators.  \
If the ACL being deleted is specific to a bucket, the operation is allowed for the bucket owners and administrators.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.DeleteDataPolicyAclRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.acl.DeleteDataPolicyAclRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified data policy ACL.  \
Whether the ACL being deleted is global (applies to all data policies current and future) or not, \
this operation is only allowed for administrators.

