com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.CreateCacheThrottleRuleRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.CreateCacheThrottleRuleRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a cache throttle rule that sets the maximum percent of cache that will be allocated to active jobs based on \
bucket id, priority and/or request type. Objects within jobs must satisfy all applicable rules before cache will be \
allocated.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.DeleteCacheThrottleRuleRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.DeleteCacheThrottleRuleRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified cache throttle rule.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.ForceFullCacheReclaimRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.cache.ForceFullCacheReclaimRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forces a full reclaim of all caches, and waits until the reclaim completes.  Cache contents that need to be \
retained since they're part of an active job will be retained.  Any cache contents that can be reclaimed will be.  \
This operation may take a very long time to complete, depending on how much of the cache can be reclaimed and \
how many blobs the cache is managing.

