com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.ModifyDataPathBackendRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.ModifyDataPathBackendRequestHandler.documentation=\
Activate the data path and/or configure automatic data path activation.  \
Setting the auto activation timeout to null disables auto activation.  \
The unavailable media policy determines the policy for how to handle "temporarily unavailable" media when \
creating GET and VERIFY jobs.  For example, consider 2 cases: (1) a blob is on tapes A and B; (2) a blob is on \
tape B.  Consider that tape B is temporarily unavailable (e.g. its tape partition is quiesced, or its library \
is powered down).  With policy ALLOW, in case 1, we could service the job from either tape A or B, and in case 2, \
we would service the job from tape B.  With policy DISCOURAGED, in case 1, we would service the job from tape A, \
and in case 2, we would service the job from tape B.  With policy DISALLOW, in case 1, we would service the job \
from tape A, and in case 2, we would fail the job creation.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.GetDataPlannerBlobStoreTasksRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.GetDataPlannerBlobStoreTasksRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the tasks we are actively working on in the backend.  \
If the full details flag is specified, will also include all queued work in the backend.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.GetDataPathBackendRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.dataplanner.GetDataPathBackendRequestHandler.documentation=\
