com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobTapesAsDegradedRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobTapesAsDegradedRequestHandler.documentation=\
Confirm that the suspected degradation is correct, marking the specified blobs as degraded.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobDs3TargetsAsDegradedRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobDs3TargetsAsDegradedRequestHandler.documentation=\
Confirm that the suspected degradation is correct, marking the specified blobs as degraded.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobS3TargetsAsDegradedRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.degradation.MarkSuspectBlobS3TargetsAsDegradedRequestHandler.documentation=\
Confirm that the suspected degradation is correct, marking the specified blobs as degraded.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateGroupGroupMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateGroupGroupMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create the specified group as a member from the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateUserGroupMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.CreateUserGroupMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create the specified user as a member from the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.DeleteGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.DeleteGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.DeleteGroupMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.DeleteGroupMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Remove the specified member from the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified group member.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupMembersRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupMembersRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all group members.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.GetGroupsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all groups.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.ModifyGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.ModifyGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified group.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.VerifyUserIsMemberOfGroupRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.group.VerifyUserIsMemberOfGroupRequestHandler.documentation=\
Verifies that the specified user is a member of the specified group.  If a user is not specified, it is \
assumed that the user making the request is the user to check for membership on.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.AllocateJobChunkRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.AllocateJobChunkRequestHandler.documentation=\
Allocate a specific job chunk that is part of a PUT job before PUT'ing the objects \
to avoid 307 retries on the object PUTs, which adversely impact DS3 server performance \
and require you to perpetually provide the object data stream on PUTs for every retry.  \
The ID that must be supplied for this request is the job chunk's ID.  \
Use of this request handler is discouraged.  See GetJobChunksReadyForClientProcessingRequestHandler for \
the preferred way to get chunks to work on, which works for both GETs and PUTs, and has Spectra managing your \
working chunk window, rather than moving that complexity to you.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelActiveJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelActiveJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delegates to the CancelJobRequestHandler

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelAllActiveJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelAllActiveJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delegates to the CancelAllJobsRequestHandler

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelAllJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelAllJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forcibly cancels all jobs that are in progress, or, if filtering parameters are specified, cancels all jobs that are in progress \
that match the specified filtering criteria.  \
Any objects in the job that have been partially written to their permanent data stores \
(regardless as to whether or not they have been completely written to cache) will be deleted and any space \
object pieces consume on permanent data stores marked as eligible for reclamation.  \
For a less forced way to cancel jobs, look at TruncateAllJobsRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CancelJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forcibly cancel a job that is in progress.  \
Any objects in the job that have been partially written to their permanent data stores \
(regardless as to whether or not they have been completely written to cache) will be deleted and any space \
object pieces consume on permanent data stores marked as eligible for reclamation.  \
For a less forced way to cancel jobs, look at TruncateJobRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ClearAllCanceledJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ClearAllCanceledJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Clears all canceled job history.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ClearAllCompletedJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ClearAllCompletedJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Clears all completed job history.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CloseAggregatingJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CloseAggregatingJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Closes an existing aggregating job so no more jobs may be appended to it.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreateGetJobRequestHandler.version=12
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreateGetJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a job to GET / read objects.  An XML payload must be sent to describe the GET job to create.  \
If not specified, the job priority and chunk client processing order guarantee will default to \
the default configured on the data policy for the bucket that the job is for.\
The NONE chunk client processing order guarantee will achieve maximum performance and does not require pre-allocation in the cache, \
but requires the client of the job to get chunks as they become available, even if they become available out of order.  \
The job will time out and be canceled if there has been no activity for the job in at least 24 hours.  \
Any of the following is considered job activity: (i) I/O transfer to the client, \
or (ii) modify job requests (even if the modify request doesn't actually modify anything).  \
Folders are not allowed to be part of a GET job (since folders are always zero-length).  \
Objects that are zero-length that are requested as part of a GET job will be ignored \
(and will not be included in the resulting GET job created).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.StageObjectsJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.StageObjectsJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a job to stage objects into the cache.  An XML payload must be sent to describe the GET job to create.  \
If not specified, the job priority and chunk client processing order guarantee will default to \
the default configured on the data policy for the bucket that the job is for.\

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreatePutJobRequestHandler.version=13
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreatePutJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a job to PUT / write objects.  An XML payload must be sent to describe the PUT job to create.  \
If not specified, the job priority and write optimization will default to \
the default configured on the data policy for the bucket that the job is for. \
In the response payload for creating a PUT job, the objects sent in the request will be broken up and organized into chunks.  \
Chunks must be sent by the client in order; however, objects within a given chunk may be sent in any order.  \
The job will time out and be canceled if there has been no activity for the job in at least 24 hours.  \
If a job is canceled due to lack of activity, it will be non-forcibly canceled, which ensures that any objects \
transmitted in their entirety by the client will be retained (and only objects that are incomplete will be canceled).  \
Any of the following is considered job activity: (i) I/O transfer from the client, \
or (ii) modify job requests (even if the modify request doesn't actually modify anything).  \
Folders (which are always zero-length) and zero-length objects must be explicitly PUT after creating a PUT job, \
which gives the client an opportunity to upload metadata for the folder or zero-length object at that time.  \
Note that, if the force flag is not specified, that VerifySafeToCreatePutJobRequestHandler will be invoked as \
a prerequisite step to creating the PUT job, to ensure it is safe to do so.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreateVerifyJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.CreateVerifyJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a job to verify objects.  An XML payload must be sent to describe the verify job to create.  \
If not specified, the job priority will default to the default \
configured on the data policy for the bucket that the job is for.  \
A verify job reads data from tape and verifies that the CRC of the data read matches the expected CRC.  Verify \
jobs will ALWAYS read from tape - even if the data currently resides in cache.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.DeleteJobCreationFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.DeleteJobCreationFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the job creation failure specified.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetActiveJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetActiveJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the specified active job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetActiveJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetActiveJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all in-progress jobs.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCanceledJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCanceledJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the specified canceled job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCanceledJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCanceledJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all canceled jobs.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCompletedJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCompletedJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all completed jobs.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCompletedJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetCompletedJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the specified completed job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunkDaoRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunkDaoRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified job chunk (just the chunk information with no information about the objects in the chunk).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunkRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunkRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified job chunk (with the node and object information for the chunk).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunksReadyForClientProcessingRequestHandler.version=12
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobChunksReadyForClientProcessingRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all job chunks for a given job that are ready for client processing.  \
For PUT jobs, this will allocate a working window of job chunks if possible and return the job chunks that the \
client can upload.  Any chunk returned is fully allocated, meaning that you do not have to handle \
307 retries on subsequent PUTs for said chunks, which adversely impacts DS3 server performance and requires \
you to perpetually attach the object data stream for every retry.  \
For GET jobs, this will respond with which job chunks have been loaded into cache and are ready for download.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobCreationFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobCreationFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the list of job creation failures.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobEntriesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobEntriesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all job entries for a given job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobRequestHandler.version=12
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified job.  The status field of the job returned will designate whether the job is IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED, or CANCELED.  \
Jobs that have completed or been canceled will be automatically cleared after 30 days.  \
A job can be canceled explicitly by a user or automatically once internal timeouts are reached due to client inactivity.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all in-progress jobs.  \
If the full details request parameter is specified, also includes recent completed and canceled jobs.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobSummaryRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobSummaryRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get a progress summary of the specified job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobToReplicateRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.GetJobToReplicateRequestHandler.documentation=\
Returns a payload that represents a job that a client desires to replicate to another Black Pearl.  This payload \
is not intended to be consumed directly by the client, but rather, to be forwarded to another Black Pearl \
to replicate the job.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ModifyActiveJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ModifyActiveJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delegates to the ModifyJobRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ModifyJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ModifyJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify a job that is in progress.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ReplicatePutJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.ReplicatePutJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Replicates a job from another Black Pearl to this Black Pearl, ensuring that the object ids, blob ids, object \
versions, and blobbing structures for each object are identical, so that the objects are recognized as \
identical across the Black Pearls that replication is performed across.  Clients must feed the response payload \
returned by GetPutJobToReplicateRequestHandler on the source Black Pearl in as the request payload for the\
ReplicatePutJobRequestHandler on the target Black Pearl.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateActiveJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateActiveJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delegates to the TruncateJobRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateAllActiveJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateAllActiveJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delegates to the TruncateAllJobsRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateAllJobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateAllJobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels all jobs that are in progress, or, if filtering parameters are specified, cancels all jobs that are in progress \
that match the specified filtering criteria.  \
Any objects in the job that have been written in their entirety to their permanent data stores will be retained.  \
For a more forced way to cancel jobs, look at CancelAllJobsRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.TruncateJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel a job that is in progress.  \
Any objects in the job that have been written in their entirety to their permanent data stores will be retained.  \
For a more forced way to cancel jobs, look at CancelJobRequestHandler.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.VerifySafeToCreatePutJobRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.job.VerifySafeToCreatePutJobRequestHandler.documentation=\
Checks to see if the specified user can safely create a PUT job for the specified bucket at this time.  \
It is not safe to create a PUT job if at least one target is offline that we need to replicate to.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.GetNodeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.GetNodeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified node.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.GetNodesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.GetNodesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all nodes.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.ModifyNodeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.node.ModifyNodeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified node.  The human and DNS names of the node can be modified.  \
If a DNS name isn't configured for a node, \
its data path IP address will be used when the TCP/IP address of the node must be given to a client.  \
If a DNS name is configured for a node, \
this DNS name (or IP address) will be used, regardless as to whether or not the data path IP address changes after the DNS name is configured.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateAzureTargetFailureNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateAzureTargetFailureNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Creates a notification registration for DS3 target failure events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateBucketChangesNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateBucketChangesNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for changes to objects in a given bucket.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateDs3TargetFailureNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateDs3TargetFailureNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Creates a notification registration for DS3 target failure events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCompletedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCompletedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for job completed events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCreatedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCreatedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for job created events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCreationFailedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateJobCreationFailedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for job creation failure events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectCachedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectCachedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for object cached events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectLostNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectLostNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for object lost events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectPersistedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreateObjectPersistedNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for object persisted events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.notification.CreatePoolFailureNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
