com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.DeleteFolderRecursivelyRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.DeleteFolderRecursivelyRequestHandler.documentation=\
Recursively deletes the folder specified and all folders and objects beneath it.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetBlobPersistenceRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetBlobPersistenceRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets existence and checksum information for the specified blob ids.  \
This request handler is intended to be used by other DS3 appliances that are replicating to this DS3 appliance.  \
This request handler is not intended to be used by end users directly.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get an S3 object.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all S3 objects.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all S3 objects with detailed information in the response payload.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetPhysicalPlacementForObjectsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetPhysicalPlacementForObjectsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the physical placement of the objects specified.  Objects are specified the same they are for creating a GET job.  \
The lack of existence of an object or the lack of its having physical placement will not result in any exception.  \
If the full_details query param is specified, physical placement will be shown on a per-object-piece basis.  \
If the full_details query param is not specified, a summary physical placement will be provided without per-object-piece breakups.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetPhysicalPlacementForObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.GetPhysicalPlacementForObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the physical placement of the objects specified.  Objects are specified the same they are for creating a GET job.  \
The lack of existence of an object or the lack of its having physical placement will not result in any exception.  \
If the full_details query param is specified, physical placement will be shown on a per-object-piece basis.  \
If the full_details query param is not specified, a summary physical placement will be provided without per-object-piece breakups.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.UndeleteObjectRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.UndeleteObjectRequestHandler.documentation=\
Undeletes an object on a versioned system if available. Can only be used on the most recent version of that object.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.VerifyPhysicalPlacementForObjectsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.VerifyPhysicalPlacementForObjectsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the physical placement of the objects specified.  Objects are specified the same they are for creating a GET job.  \
A 404 not found error will be returned if one or more objects either (i) does not exist, or (ii) has no physical placement.  \
If the full_details query param is specified, physical placement will be shown on a per-object-piece basis.  \
If the full_details query param is not specified, a summary physical placement will be provided without per-object-piece breakups.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.VerifyPhysicalPlacementForObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.object.VerifyPhysicalPlacementForObjectsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the physical placement of the objects specified.  Objects are specified the same they are for creating a GET job.  \
A 404 not found error will be returned if one or more objects either (i) does not exist, or (ii) has no physical placement.  \
If the full_details query param is specified, physical placement will be shown on a per-object-piece basis.  \
If the full_details query param is not specified, a summary physical placement will be provided without per-object-piece breakups.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelImportOnAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelImportOnAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel all pending pool imports.  Imports that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelImportPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelImportPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel a pending pool import on the specified pool.  If the import has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelVerifyOnAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelVerifyOnAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel all pending pool verifications.  Verifies that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelVerifyPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CancelVerifyPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel a pending pool verification on the specified pool.  If the verify has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CompactAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CompactAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Pool compaction is done automatically, periodically in the background.  Forces a compaction to be scheduled \
immediately for all eligible pools, without having to wait for the automatic, periodic scheduling.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CompactPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CompactPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Pool compaction is done automatically, periodically in the background.  When a pool is compacted, it is first \
checked to see if it can be reclaimed in its entirety and unassigned from its assigned storage domain, making \
it available to be allocated to any storage domain.  A pool can only be reclaimed in its entirety if it contains \
no data on it.  If the pool cannot be reclaimed in its entirety, its usage level will be checked and data that \
is eligible for deletion will be deleted as necessary to compact the pool down to where it has plenty of space \
for new data.  Forces a compaction to be scheduled immediately, without having to wait for the automatic, periodic \
scheduling of compaction.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CreatePoolPartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.CreatePoolPartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a pool partition.  A pool partition may contain any number of pools and may be added as a member of a storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeallocatePoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeallocatePoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deallocates the specified pool, which contains no data.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePermanentlyLostPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePermanentlyLostPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified pool which has been permanently lost, recording any data loss that has occurred as a result.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePoolFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePoolFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified pool failure.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePoolPartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.DeletePoolPartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified pool partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ForcePoolEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ForcePoolEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forces the pool environment to be refreshed at the earliest convenience.  Note that the pool \
environment is updated automatically based on pool environment change events.  Invoking this method \
should never be necessary unless an event is missed and thus we fail to update the pool environment.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.FormatAllForeignPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.FormatAllForeignPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Formats all foreign pools, permanently deleting all data on them and taking ownership of them for this appliance.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.FormatForeignPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.FormatForeignPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Formats the specified foreign pool, permanently deleting all data on it and taking ownership of it for this appliance.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetBlobsOnPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetBlobsOnPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the object pieces on the specified pool.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all pool failures.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolPartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolPartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified pool partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolPartitionsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolPartitionsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all pool partitions.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified pool.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.GetPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all pools.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ImportAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ImportAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports all foreign Black Pearl pools.  Note that this will not import a pool that has arbitrary data not from a Black Pearl on it.  \
If one of more buckets being imported does not exist yet, the user ID and data policy to use for any buckets \
that have to be created must be specified.  The storage domain to ingress the pool into may optionally \
be specified.  If not specified, the system will attempt to automatically determine the most sane storage \
domain to place the pool into.  \
It is highly recommended to verify data prior to import whenever it's possible that what's being imported \
may contain objects with the same name in the same bucket as an already existing object that's different.  \
Without verifying data prior to import, it is possible for the old object to be replaced with the one being \
imported, even if the one being imported is partially corrupt and cannot be read.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ImportPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ImportPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports the specified foreign Black Pearl pool.  Note that this will not import a pool that has arbitrary data not from a Black Pearl on it.  \
If one of more buckets being imported does not exist yet, the user ID and data policy to use for any buckets \
that have to be created must be specified.  The storage domain to ingress the pool into may optionally \
be specified.  If not specified, the system will attempt to automatically determine the most sane storage \
domain to place the pool into.  \
It is highly recommended to verify data prior to import whenever it's possible that what's being imported \
may contain objects with the same name in the same bucket as an already existing object that's different.  \
Without verifying data prior to import, it is possible for the old object to be replaced with the one being \
imported, even if the one being imported is partially corrupt and cannot be read.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modifies the quiesced state across all pools to the value specified.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyPoolPartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyPoolPartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified pool partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.ModifyPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified pool.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.VerifyAllPoolsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.VerifyAllPoolsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Pool verification is done automatically, periodically in the background.  Forces a verification to be scheduled \
immediately for all eligible pools, without having to wait for the automatic, periodic scheduling.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.VerifyPoolRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.pool.VerifyPoolRequestHandler.documentation=\
Pool verification is done automatically, periodically in the background.  When a pool is verified, blobs that \
should be persisted on the pool are checked to ensure they do exist and are valid.  If a blob is missing or is \
otherwise invalid, a blob loss failure shall be generated.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ConvertStorageDomainToDs3TargetRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ConvertStorageDomainToDs3TargetRequestHandler.documentation=\
Converts the specified storage domain to the specified DS3 target.  Once converted, there is no conversion back.  \
In converting the storage domain over, all blobs persisted locally will be migrated to be persisted at the target.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreatePoolStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreatePoolStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Adds the specified pool partition as a member of the specified storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreateStorageDomainRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreateStorageDomainRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreateTapeStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.CreateTapeStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Adds the specified tape partition / tape type combination as a member of the specified storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified storage domain failure.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified storage domain member.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.DeleteStorageDomainRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all storage domain failures.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the specified storage domain member.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainMembersRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainMembersRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all storage domain members.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the specified storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.GetStorageDomainsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all storage domains.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ModifyStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ModifyStorageDomainMemberRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified storage domain member.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ModifyStorageDomainRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.storagedomain.ModifyStorageDomainRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified storage domain.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetAbmConfigRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetAbmConfigRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets info about the current ABM (Advanced Bucket Management) configuration.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.ForceFeatureKeyValidationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.ForceFeatureKeyValidationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forces a synchronous feature key validation.  Feature keys are validated regularly automatically, and invoking \
this request handler shouldn't ever be necessary to an end user, as validation will never re-enable a disabled \
key (it can only disable an enabled key).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetFeatureKeysRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetFeatureKeysRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets all feature keys.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetRequestHandlersFormalApiContractRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetRequestHandlersFormalApiContractRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets a formal contract for the API that can be easily parsed.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetRequestHandlersRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetRequestHandlersRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get information (and self-documentation) on all the request handlers supported by your DS3 server.  \
Note that the version for a request handler is always of the form X.Y, where X is the major revision and Y\
is the minor revision.  The major revision is always an integer.  The minor revision is always an MD5 checksum.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetSystemFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetSystemFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the current system failures that must be fixed.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetSystemInformationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.GetSystemInformationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get basic system information, including version and build information, and the system serial number.\
Note that the version is always of the form X.Y, where X is the MD5 checksum across all request handler major\
revisions and Y is the MD5 checksum across all request handler full versions (including the minor revision).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.ResetInstanceIdentifierRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.ResetInstanceIdentifierRequestHandler.documentation=\
Resets and regenerates the instance identifier.  Resetting the instance identifier is only necessary in rare \
circumstances where there are two branches of an instance running at the same time.  Of of the two branches must \
have its instance identifier reset if the two instances are to replicate between each other.  The most common \
occurrence of this is when one instance is initially configured with dual copy where one copy goes on one \
library and the other copy goes on the other, then a new Black Pearl is added and one library and the new BP \
moved to another physical location.  In this case, both BPs would start with the same database and each would \
have the persistence rule and storage domain for the remote library converted to a replication rule.  \
This requires that one or both sites have their instance identifier reset first.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.VerifySystemHealthRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.system.VerifySystemHealthRequestHandler.documentation=\
Verifies that the system appears to be online and functioning normally.  If critical components in the\
data path front end are unresponsive, an error will be generated.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelEjectOnAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelEjectOnAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels all pending tape ejects.  Ejects that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelEjectTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelEjectTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels a pending tape eject on the specified tape.  If the eject has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelFormatOnAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelFormatOnAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel all pending tape formats.  Formats that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelFormatTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelFormatTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel a pending tape format on the specified tape.  If the format has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelImportOnAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelImportOnAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel all pending tape imports.  Imports that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelImportTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelImportTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancel a pending tape import on the specified tape.  If the import has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelOnlineOnAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelOnlineOnAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels all pending tape onlining.  Onlining that has already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelOnlineTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelOnlineTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels a pending tape onlining on the specified tape.  If the eject has already begun to be brought online, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelTestTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelTestTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels any pending test on the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelVerifyOnAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelVerifyOnAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels all pending tape verifications.  Verifications that have already begun cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelVerifyTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CancelVerifyTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cancels a pending tape verification on the specified tape.  If the verify has already begun, it cannot be cancelled.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CleanTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CleanTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Cleans the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CreateDriveDumpRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CreateDriveDumpRequestHandler.documentation=\
Creates a drive dump of the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CreateTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.CreateTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a directive for formatting tapes of a particular type at the specified density for the specified partition.  \
The density specified is the tape drive type that the tape should be compatible with.  \
The tape will be formatted at the highest density supported by the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeletePermanentlyLostTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeletePermanentlyLostTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified tape which has been permanently lost, recording any data loss that has occurred as a result.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified tape density directive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified offline tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapeFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified tape failure.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapePartitionFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapePartitionFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified tape partition failure.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapePartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.DeleteTapePartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified offline tape partition.  \
Any tapes that had data on them in that partition will be de-associated from the partition.  \
Any tapes without data on them and tape drives that were associated with the partition will be deleted.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Ejects all tapes that are eligible to be ejected.  If a tape is in use, it will be ejected once it is no longer in use.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectStorageDomainBlobsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectStorageDomainBlobsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Ejects all tapes that are eligible to be ejected within the storage domain specified for the blob payload included.  \
If a tape is in use, it will be ejected once it is no longer in use.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectStorageDomainRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectStorageDomainRequestHandler.documentation=\
Ejects all tapes that are eligible to be ejected within the storage domain specified.  If a tape is in use, it will be ejected once it is no longer in use.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.EjectTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Ejects the tape specified.  If the tape is in use, it will be ejected once it is no longer in use.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ForceTapeEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ForceTapeEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forces the tape environment to be refreshed at the earliest convenience.  Note that the tape \
environment is updated automatically based on tape environment change events.  Invoking this method \
should never be necessary unless an event is missed and thus we fail to update the tape environment.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.FormatAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.FormatAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Format all tapes that have not already been formatted and are not already in use by the system.  \
Tapes that contain data written externally of this product will be formatted even without the force flag.  \
Tapes that contain data written by this product (but not this specific appliance) will not be formatted unless the force flag is specified.  \
Tapes that contain data written by this appliance cannot be deleted in this manner.  You must delete the objects and/or buckets before you can format the tape they reside on.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.FormatTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.FormatTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Format the specified tape if it has not already been formatted and is not already in use by the system.  \
Tapes that contain data written externally of this product will be formatted even without the force flag.  \
Tapes that contain data written by this product (but not this specific appliance) will not be formatted unless the force flag is specified.  \
Tapes that contain data written by this appliance cannot be deleted in this manner.  You must delete the objects and/or buckets before you can format the tape they reside on.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetBlobsOnTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetBlobsOnTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the object pieces on the specified tape.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDensityDirectiveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape density directive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDensityDirectivesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDensityDirectivesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape density directives.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDrivesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeDrivesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape drives.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape failures.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeLibrariesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeLibrariesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape libraries.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeLibraryRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeLibraryRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape library.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionFailuresRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionFailuresRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape partition failures.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape partitions.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapePartitionsWithFullDetailsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tape partitions with full details in the response payload.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified tape.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.GetTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all tapes.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ImportAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ImportAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports all foreign Black Pearl tapes.  Note that this will not import tapes that have arbitrary data not from a Black Pearl on them.  \
If one of more buckets being imported does not exist yet, the user ID and data policy to use for any buckets \
that have to be created must be specified.  The storage domain to ingress the tape into may optionally \
be specified.  If not specified, the system will attempt to automatically determine the most sane storage \
domain to place the tape into.  \
It is highly recommended to verify data prior to import whenever it's possible that what's being imported \
may contain objects with the same name in the same bucket as an already existing object that's different.  \
Without verifying data prior to import, it is possible for the old object to be replaced with the one being \
imported, even if the one being imported is partially corrupt and cannot be read.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ImportTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ImportTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports the specified foreign Black Pearl tape.  Note that this will not import a tape that has arbitrary data not from a Black Pearl on it.  \
If one of more buckets being imported does not exist yet, the user ID and data policy to use for any buckets \
that have to be created must be specified.  The storage domain to ingress the tape into may optionally \
be specified.  If not specified, the system will attempt to automatically determine the most sane storage \
domain to place the tape into.  \
It is highly recommended to verify data prior to import whenever it's possible that what's being imported \
may contain objects with the same name in the same bucket as an already existing object that's different.  \
Without verifying data prior to import, it is possible for the old object to be replaced with the one being \
imported, even if the one being imported is partially corrupt and cannot be read.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.InspectAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.InspectAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Inspect all tapes that are not already queued to be inspected.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.InspectTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.InspectTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Inspect the specified tape if it has not already been queued to be inspected.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.MarkTapeForCompactionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.MarkTapeForCompactionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Manually mark a tape to be included in the next compaction cycle.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapePartitionRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapePartitionRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified tape partition.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyAllTapePartitionsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyAllTapePartitionsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified property for all tape partitions.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.ModifyTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Modify the specified tape.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.OnlineAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.OnlineAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Onlines all tapes that are eligible to be onlined.  Tapes that show up in import/export slots must be onlined before they can be used.  Onlining a tape moves it to a storage slot.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.OnlineTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.OnlineTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Onlines the tape specified.  Tapes that show up in import/export slots must be onlined before they can be used.  Onlining a tape moves it to a storage slot.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.RawImportAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.RawImportAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports all non-Black Pearl foreign tapes.  Use ImportAllTapesRequestHandler to import all Black Pearl foreign \
tapes.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.RawImportTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.RawImportTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Imports the specified non-Black Pearl foreign tapes.  Use ImportTapeRequestHandler to import Black Pearl \
foreign tapes.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.TestTapeDriveRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.TestTapeDriveRequestHandler.documentation=\
Tests the specified tape drive.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.VerifyAllTapesRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.VerifyAllTapesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Verifies the media contents across all tapes (this may take a very long time).

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.VerifyTapeRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.tape.VerifyTapeRequestHandler.documentation=\
Verifies the media contents on the specified tape.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.ForceTargetEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.ForceTargetEnvironmentRefreshRequestHandler.documentation=\
Forces the target environment to be refreshed immediately and synchronously.  Note that the target \
environment is updated automatically based on a polling interval, so manual refreshes shouldn't be necessary \
unless there is an impatient consumer.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.CreateAzureTargetBucketNameRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.CreateAzureTargetBucketNameRequestHandler.documentation=\
Defines a custom bucket name mapping between a local BP bucket and a Microsoft Azure target blob container.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.CreateAzureTargetReadPreferenceRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.CreateAzureTargetReadPreferenceRequestHandler.documentation=\
Creates a Microsoft Azure read preference that overrides the default read preference of the target.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetBucketNameRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetBucketNameRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes a Microsoft Azure custom bucket name mapping between a local BP bucket and a Microsoft Azure target blob container.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetFailureRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetFailureRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified failure.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetReadPreferenceRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetReadPreferenceRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes a Microsoft Azure read preference that overrides the default read preference of the target.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrads3.target.azure.DeleteAzureTargetRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes the specified Microsoft Azure target.

