com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.cache.GetCacheEntriesRequestHandler.documentation=\
Gets the utilization and cache contents across all caches in the system.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.CreateGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.CreateGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a notification registration for generic dao events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.DeleteGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.DeleteGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete a notification registration for generic dao events.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.GetGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.GetGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get the specified notification registration.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.GetGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationsRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.notification.GetGenericDaoNotificationRegistrationsRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all notification registrations of this type.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.CreateFeatureKeyRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.CreateFeatureKeyRequestHandler.documentation=\
Creates / installs the specified feature key.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.CreateHeapDumpRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.CreateHeapDumpRequestHandler.documentation=\
Generate a heap dump for the specified application.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.DeleteFeatureKeyRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.DeleteFeatureKeyRequestHandler.documentation=\
Deletes / removes the specified feature key.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.GetBeansRetrieverBeansRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.GetBeansRetrieverBeansRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all beans from the specified beans retriever defined in the dao layer.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.GetBeansRetrieversRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.GetBeansRetrieversRequestHandler.documentation=\
Get all beans retrievers defined in the dao layer.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.QuiesceDataPathToPrepareForShutdownRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.system.QuiesceDataPathToPrepareForShutdownRequestHandler.documentation=\
Quiesces the data path to prepare it for shutdown.  The data path cannot be un-quiesced without restarting it.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.tape.CreateFakeTapeEnvironmentRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.tape.CreateFakeTapeEnvironmentRequestHandler.documentation=\
This is for testing purposes only e.g. test clients may want to be able to create a data policy without a \
real backend.  This will allow them to create a mocked tape backend they can create a storage domain \
using so that they can create the data policy to use.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.user.CreateUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.user.CreateUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Create a user.

com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.user.DeleteUserRequestHandler.version=1
com.spectralogic.s3.server.handler.reqhandler.spectrainternal.user.DeleteUserRequestHandler.documentation=\
Delete the specified user.
